HEADWORD: Thomsens disease
<hw>Thom"sen's dis*ease"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From
<etsep>Thomsen</etsep>, a physician of Sleswick.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An affection apparently congenital, consisting in
tonic contraction and stiffness of the voluntary muscles occurring after
a period of muscular inaction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thomsonian</ent>⟦br⟧
